    "text":  "fought them before, and I\u0027ll do it again, but right now I\u0027ve got bigger fish to fry. I mean literally— there\u0027s a fish in the teachers\u0027 parking lot that\u0027s the size of a school bus.\" Margot groaned and climbed out. As she was scraping sloppy joe off her shirt, she saw Alex, the tallest kid in school. As the spotlight began to swing toward her, an idea popped into her head. She ran over to Alex and crouched in his shadow. Wherever Alex moved, Margot moved. Her fancy footwork was actually quite impressive. She was so sneaky that Alex didn\u0027t even notice she was there. At one point, he did feel like someone was 16 following him and spun around like a dog chasing its own tail, but Margot moved in sync with him. She was very happy she had read The Art of Camouflage and 101 Neat Ninja Facts. She cautiously peered around Alex and could see the spotlight heading toward the other side of the Cafetorium. I did it! I figured out a solution! Margot thought. Just then, Alex pushed open the door to the boys\u0027 restroom and went inside. Margot was desperate to escape. But not that desperate. The spotlight swung around again and caught Margot in its beam. She scurried like a panicked squirrel,",
